      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STARBASE (2) has been tackling stronger company of late, leading from this barrier and sticking on okay last time to follow three successive placings at this circuit and distance. He is suited back in maiden grade. SPARTAN CHIMES (4) is at the track for the first time. By King Of Swing and hails from the John O'Shea stable. Was not far away from the handy filly Shes A Delaney in a recent trial here so looks to have ability. MCWEAPON (1) made an encouraging return when he came from a wide barrier for third at Newcastle. Fitter for that and should enjoy an economical run from the inside draw. Leading hope. MISTER MANFREDI (3) chased solidly enough for fourth at this circuit and distance at his first race start. Strips fitter and draws well so can improve.",
